name: Crash Hounds Of America "Sewer Loving"
description:
You get a lucky number of 13 tracks on this lo-fi cassette which may be the food baby of one or more individuals. I think they probably listen to Uzi Rash and eat a lot of pizza while reading cool zines. 
To describe the sound I would call this minimal punk wave without the seriousness, possibly "Tunes For The Humorously Depressed". Listen to it on your Walkman while riding the bus to meet your rad lady/dude or while on a date with yourself.

Released by HOT & READY RECORDS in 2013

name: Drive-Thru Mystics "Brick"
description: Cassette tape of live and studio recordings from a fun Sacramento band that plays a blend of catchy rock 'n roll with psychedelic undertones and hard hitting garage aesthetics. Approximately 58 min long and includes free download code.
